article.description: Rio Haskett and Robert Baker scored 14 points apiece as Harvard rolled past Maine 67-46 on Sunday.
article.headline: Haskett scores 14 to lead Harvard over Maine 67-46
article.linkText: Haskett scores 14 to lead Harvard over Maine 67-46
article.story: BOSTON -- Rio Haskett and Robert Baker scored 14 points apiece as Harvard rolled past Maine 67-46 on Sunday. Chris Lewis added 10 points for the Crimson (2-1), who shot 53% from the floor (26 of 49). Justin Bassey had three of Harvard's 12 steals in the game. Sergio El Darwich led the Black Bears (1-1) with 18 points. Nedeljko Prijovic pitched in with 11 points and 12 rebounds, while Andrew Fleming scored 10. Maine made just 17 of 50 shots from the floor (34%), including 4 of 15 from 3-point range (27%). Harvard is coming off its seventh Ivy League championship in the past nine years and returned 97 percent of its scoring from last season. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
